<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-458-205  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 458 205.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC-Computing  Oct 1990 v3 n10 p56(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Frenetic phonetics. (WordPerfect Rhymer electronic rhymingdictionary)(What's Up!) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>DeJean, David.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   WordPerfect Corp. (product introduction).andO;Product:   WordPerfect Rhymer (Computer program) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     DictionariesWord processing softwareMemory-Resident SoftwareProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>The WordPerfect Corporation probably doesn't top your list of fun softwarecompanies.andP;  But here it is, introducing WordPerfect Rhymer.andP;  We may all haveto revise our lists.andM;WordPerfect's $79 &quot;phonetic word finder&quot; goes way beyond what a thesaurusdoes.andP;  it installs as a TSR and uses a 90,000-word lexicon.andP;  And it findsrhymes.andP;  Not just end-of-word rhymes, but words that alliterate with thetarget word.andP;  it also does first-syllable sound matching, double and triplerhymes and more.andM;To use it, replace letters and parts of the target word with wildcardmarkers.andP;  WordPerfect Rhymer then builds lists of words that match itsphonetic analysis.andP;  How to use this package is the easy part.andP;  What to use itfor isn't.andP;  The Orem, Utah, software company says the program is forwordsmiths-educators, writers, editors, linguists, songwriters.andP;  it may alsoturn out to be a great party game (801-225-5000).andO;</TEXT></DOC>